10 SECTION 1. Section 2 of this 2026 Act is added to and made a part of ORS 475C.005 to
11 475C.525.
12 SECTION 2. (1)(a) As used in this section, “container” means the innermost wrapping,
13 packaging or vessel in direct contact with a final marijuana item in which the final
14 marijuana item product is enclosed for retail sale to a consumer.
15 (b) “Container” does not mean a bulk shipping container or outer wrapping that are not
16 essential for the final retail delivery or sale of the marijuana item to a consumer for personal
17 use.
18 (2) The Oregon Liquor and Cannabis Commission shall ensure that the concentration
19 limit of adult use cannabinoids established by rule under ORS 475C.009 (20) includes a per
20 container concentration limit of adult use cannabinoids.
