33 table glycerin, vegetable oils, animal fats, isopropyl alcohol or ethanol;
34 (c) A chemical extraction process using carbon dioxide, provided that the process does not in-
35 volve the use of high heat or pressure; or
36 (d) Any other process identified by the commission, in consultation with the authority, by rule.
37 (6) “Cannabinoid edible” means food or potable liquid into which a cannabinoid concentrate,
38 cannabinoid extract or dried marijuana leaves or flowers have been incorporated.
