5 SECTION 17. Sections 18 and 19 of this 2026 Act are added to and made a part of ORS
6 571.260 to 571.348.
7 SECTION 18. (1) The State Department of Agriculture may not issue a license to grow
8 or handle industrial hemp under ORS 571.281 unless the applicant submits with the applica-
9 tion a statement accurately identifying the legal address and owner of the premises at which
10 the industrial hemp operation will be located and the requirements of subsections (2) and (3)
11 of this section are met.
12 (2) The department shall independently verify the information provided under subsection
13 (1) of this section regarding the ownership of the premises described in subsection (1) of this
14 section with the county in which the premises is located.
15 (3) If the applicant described in subsection (1) of this section is not the owner of the
16 premises described in subsection (1) of this section, the applicant shall:
17 (a) Inform the owner in writing that the premises is intended to be the location of an
18 industrial hemp operation for which the applicant is licensed;
19 (b) If the owner wishes to consent to the use of the premises for the purposes of growing
20 or handling industrial hemp, obtain from the owner the owner’s written signature, witnessed
21 by a notary public, confirming ownership of the premises and consenting to the use of the
22 premises for the purpose of growing or handling industrial hemp; and
23 (c) Provide the owner’s witnessed signature as described in paragraph (b) of this sub-
24 section to the department.
25 (4) An owner who consents as described in subsection (3) of this section to the use of the
26 owner’s premises for the purpose of growing or handling industrial hemp may specify in the
27 document that contains the owner’s witnessed signature the number of licensure terms for
28 which the owner’s consent to the use of the premises is valid.
29 (5) The department shall cancel an application for a license to grow or handle industrial
30 hemp under ORS 571.281 if the department:
31 (a) Is not able to verify ownership of the premises described in subsection (1) of this
32 section; or
33 (b) Does not receive, if the application is from an applicant described in subsection (3)
34 of this section, the witnessed signature described in subsection (3) of this section.
35 (6) The department may adopt rules to carry out this section. Rules adopted under this
36 section may include rules to establish a form for the purposes of this section.
37 SECTION 19. (1) An applicant for an industrial hemp grower license under ORS 571.281
38 shall include with the application a land use compatibility statement from the city or county
39 that authorizes the land use in the jurisdiction in which the applicant intends to locate the
40 industrial hemp operation. The land use compatibility statement must demonstrate that the
41 industrial hemp operation is a land use that is allowable as a permitted or conditional use
42 within the given zoning designation where the land is located. The State Department of Ag-
43 riculture may not issue a license to the applicant if the land use compatibility statement
44 shows that the proposed land use is prohibited in the applicable zone.
45 (2) A city or county that receives a request for a land use compatibility statement under
[16]

HB 4139
1 this section must act on the request within 21 days of:
2 (a) Receipt of the request, if the land use is allowable as an outright permitted use; or
3 (b) Final local permit approval, if the land use is allowable as a conditional use.
4 (3) A city or county action concerning a land use compatibility statement under this
5 section is not a land use decision as that term is defined in ORS 197.015.
