16 person.
17 (b) If the crop described in paragraph (a) of this subsection is removed and the department de-
18 termines that the violation is resolved, the person described in paragraph (a) of this subsection may
19 apply for a license under ORS 571.281.
20 (2) If a person plants an industrial hemp crop or commits a violation of ORS 571.260 to 571.348
21 prior to being issued a grower license under ORS 571.281, the department shall:
22 (a)(A) Prioritize the person’s industrial hemp crop for inspection under ORS 571.281 [(7)] (8), if
23 the person planted the industrial hemp crop as described in this subsection; and
24 (B) Require the person to enter into a corrective action plan with the department; or
25 (b) Refuse to issue a license to the person if the department determines that a corrective action
26 plan is insufficient to address the violation.
27 (3) If the person described in subsection (2) of this section does not enter into a corrective
28 action plan pursuant to subsection (2) of this section, the department may not issue a license to the
29 person under ORS 571.281.
30 (4) The department may adopt rules to carry out this section, including rules to establish the
31 corrective action plan described in subsection (2) of this section.
32
33 MISCELLANEOUS
34
35 SECTION 26. ORS 475C.730 is added to and made a part of ORS 475C.670 to 475C.734.
36 SECTION 27. ORS 571.280 is added to and made a part of ORS 571.260 to 571.348.
37
38 CAPTIONS
39
40 SECTION 28. The unit captions used in this 2026 Act are provided only for the conven-
41 ience of the reader and do not become part of the statutory law of this state or express any
42 legislative intent in the enactment of this 2026 Act.
43
44 EFFECTIVE DATE
45
[19]

HB 4139
1 SECTION 29. This 2026 Act takes effect on the 91st day after the date on which the 2026
2 regular session of the Eighty-third Legislative Assembly adjourns sine die.
